KnowledgeBase.Title: Example Void compareLE 008
KnowledgeBase.RelatedFunctions: compare compareEQ compareNE compareGT compareGE compareLT

Example.Description: These examples use the compareLE function to compare two objects and return the Boolean value, true or false. The values of each object are compared to determine whether the first object is lesser than or equal in value than the second object.

Syntax.Note: The uninitialized value of x is equal to #void.
The value #void is lesser than the value of the String.
